{"lemma":"عَبُّ","slug":"عَبُّ","root":"ع.ب.ب","root_slug":"ع-ب-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ب-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n27749","n27755","n27907"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%8F%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to gulp, to chug down","examples":[{"text":"وهي الساعة التي يكون فيها مزاجه رائقاً بعد أن يكون قد عبّ ثلاثة أقداح من الويسكي.","english":"It was the hour where he had a buoyant mood already after swigging three stoops of whiskey."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"breast pocket, a pocket in a shirt higher than a جَيْب (jayb)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"light"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Considered a vulgar word; probably from Aramaic עוּבָּא / עֻבָּא / ܥܘܒܐ (ʿubbā), broader of meaning: “bosom, lap; any enclosed space; calyx …”. Doublet of غُبّ (ḡubb, “depressed terrain; bosom of the sea”). جَيْب (jayb, “pocket”) is similarly suspect of being an Aramaic borrowing.\n\nCognate with Akkadian 𒅁𒁍 (ebbu) \"to be bright, shiny; to be pure, clean\"."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n27749","headword_ar":"عَبَّ","root":"Eb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, O, Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eab~N","text_ar":"عَبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, O, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man, Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"drank"},{"kind":"text","text":"water"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without taking breath:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, Msb, TA; and T in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Env","text_ar":"عنث"},{"kind":"text","text":": [this is the sense in which it is generally used:]) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he drank"},{"kind":"text","text":"water"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without sipping"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sucking in"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino gayori maS~K","text_ar":"مِنْ غَيْرِ مَصٍّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"): (S, O:) thus, (S, O, Msb,) in the manner termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eab~N","text_ar":"عَبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O,) i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino gayori maS~K","text_ar":"مِنْ غَيْرِ مَصٍّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) the pigeon drinks water, like horses and similar beasts; (S, O, Msb;) whereas other birds take it sip after sip: (Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he drank"},{"kind":"text","text":"water"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at once, without interrupting the swallowing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"AA says, the pigeon drinks thus; differing from the other birds; for these drink by little and little: (Mgh:) [in like manner also] Esh-Sháfi'ee says, the pigeon is a bird that drinks in the manner termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eab~N","text_ar":"عَبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and cooes; for it does not drink like other birds, by little and little: (TA:) and it is said in a trad. that the livercomplaint ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlkubaAd","text_ar":"الكُبَاد"},{"kind":"text","text":") is occasioned by drinking in the manner termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eab~N","text_ar":"عَبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, O, TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eab~N","text_ar":"عَبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies [simply] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"drinking"},{"kind":"text","text":"water: or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gulping,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"swallowing down:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"doing so uninterruptedly:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"drinking"},{"kind":"text","text":"water"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a single stream, without interruption:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"drinking with the mouth from a place,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vessel, containing water, not with the hands nor with a vessel:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eab~a fiY AlmaA='i","text_ar":"عَبَّ فِى المَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY AlA_inaA='i","text_ar":"فِى الاـِنَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he so drank of the water,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the vessel:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [accord. to some] one says of a bird,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eab~a","text_ar":"عَبَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ariba","text_ar":"شَرِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) [but] Es-Sarakustee says, one does not say of a bird"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ariba AlmaA='a","text_ar":"شَرِبَ المَا=ءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HasaAhu","text_ar":"حَسَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$rb","text_ar":"شرب"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaEub~u fiyhi miyzaAbaAni","text_ar":"يَعُبُّ فِيهِ مِيزَابَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in a trad. respecting the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawoD","text_ar":"حَوْض"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. Mohammad's pool], as some relate it, means ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Two spouts"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"were pouring forth into it with an uninterrupted pouring:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but accord. to the relation commonly known, the verb is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ygt~","text_ar":"يغتّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yagut~u","text_ar":"يَغُتُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in this sense, but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yagit~u","text_ar":"يَغِتُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in another sense, as meaning the making a murmuring sound,] with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"g","text_ar":"غ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eab~ati Ald~alowu","text_ar":"عَبَّتِ الدَّلْوُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) [aor., app."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEib~u","text_ar":"تَعِبُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eab~N","text_ar":"عَبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TK,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The bucket made a sound in lading out the water."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eab~a AlbaHoru","text_ar":"عَبَّ البَحْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EubaAbN","text_ar":"عُبَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The sea rose high, with multitudinous waves."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) [Accord. to Golius,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eab~a","text_ar":"عَبَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of the sea means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It had broken waves:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but for this he has named no authority.] ―         -b5-  And [hence,] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eab~a EubaAbuhu","text_ar":"عَبَّ عُبَابُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His speech was continual and abundant."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EababN","text_ar":"عَبَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[an inf. n., of which the verb, accord. to general analogy, is app."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eab~a","text_ar":"عَبَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", first pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eabibotu","text_ar":"عَبِبْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaEab~u","text_ar":"يَعَبُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] means [The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"interrupting in swallowing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"interrupting the swallowing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eab~a","text_ar":"عَبَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [aor., app.,"},{"kind":"text","text":",] said of a plant,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It became tall."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) ―         -b2-  And [said of a man]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His face became beautiful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"comely, after having become altered."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Mgh","O","Msb","K","TA","TK"]},{"entry_id":"n27755","headword_ar":"عُبٌّ","root":"Eb","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rudonN","text_ar":"رُدْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, K,) which means The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"base"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSol","text_ar":"اَصْل"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the sleeve:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S and K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rdn","text_ar":"ردن"},{"kind":"text","text":":) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fore part of the sleeve of the shirt:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M in that art.:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lower part thereof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M in that art., and Har pp. 149 and 390:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sleeve altogether:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M in that art.:) but, as MF says, it is a vulgar word. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["O","K"]},{"entry_id":"n27907","headword_ar":"عَبٌ","root":"Ebw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"light"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the sun; (IAar, TA, and O and K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EbA^","text_ar":"عبا"},{"kind":"text","text":";) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EabowN","text_ar":"عَبْوٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is the original form; (TA;) and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eabo'N","text_ar":"عَبْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAar, and O and K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EbA^","text_ar":"عبا"},{"kind":"text","text":",) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eab~N","text_ar":"عَبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (O and K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eb","text_ar":"عب"},{"kind":"text","text":";) and IAar says that ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EabowapN","text_ar":"عَبْوَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same: (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EbA^","text_ar":"عبا"},{"kind":"text","text":":) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"light and beauty"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof: (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EbY","text_ar":"عبى"},{"kind":"text","text":":) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EibFY","text_ar":"عِبًى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]}}